Input image should be in pgm format.

To complie the programs, use:
gcc HideMessage.c -o HideMessage -lm
gcc ShowMessage.c -o ShowMessage -lm

Hide Message:
Purpose: Given a text message and an image, the text is stored in the last bit of each pixel.
Author: Sahil Gupta
Parameters: [input image filename] [“Message to hide”]
Date: 08/04/2017

Show Message:
Purpose: Given an input image, which has a text hidden in it the program decrypts the text message.
Author: Sahil Gupta
Parameters: [input image filename]
Date: 08/04/2017
